Results.ReviewText: I have always loved my coffee but recenty due to a few health issues have had to cut back on caffeine. I thought it would be very challenging as I really missed my coffee but someone suggested trying the decaf coffee. I thought I'd give it a try so that helps with my withdrawal symptoms. I tried quite a few decaf coffees but this by far is the best one. Love the smoothness taste and aroma.
Results.Title: Smooth, excellent taste and aroma

Results.ReviewText: I recently found out that I'm pregnant so instantly had to give up my normal coffee habits. As Iove the taste and small I decided to try the decaf version of Nescafe so I could still enjoy my daily coffee without the caffine. It's delicious and I certainly couldn't tell the difference!
Results.Title: Delicious alternative to vaccinated!

Results.ReviewText:
As a keen Coffee drinker, I have always liked Nescafé products but found I was drinking a lot of coffee. So decided to try decaf for my health kick year. 
I was surprised on the flavour quality as being decaf. Some other makes loose the flavour and tastes different. 
So on my list for the future is Nescafe decaf coffee,
Quality coffee which is my favourite and full of flavour too.
Results.Title: Best on the market

Results.ReviewText: Ok, so my daughter thought I shouldnt have so much caffeine and as she knows that Nescafe is my favourite brand she bought me a jar of Original DeCaff to try. Before I tried it I thought I wouldnt like it but guess what, it was really good  :)  Now I'm buying both and having original before 1pm and DeCaff anytime after. I'm so pleased I tried it and now I tell others to try it too.
Results.Title: DeCaff????  Reallly????

Results.ReviewText: Had to switch to decaf for medical reasons thought oh where do I start tried decaf years ago an just did not like the taste. I started with the more expensive brands thinking they would have a more true coffee taste but how wrong was I? Finally tried Nescafe Original Decaf and there my search ended, the taste is superb no coffee taste missing and a great price too. Thanks Nescafe.
Results.Title: Lovely taste

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks very much for letting us know.

Results.ReviewText:
I was suprised at the lack of flavour in this decaffeinated coffee as I have tried the  Nescafe original and found it much more appealing.    
It is not as expensive as some of the other coffees available, however,  I prefer a stronger flavoured coffee and would pay more for a coffee that has more body and strength.   Nescafe Alta Rica is my usual choice of  instant coffee.
Results.Title: Disappointed with lack of flavour

Results.ReviewText: After reading about the effects of too much caffeine, I sought a tasty alternative to my morning coffees. Many brands later, I had almost given up hope of finding one i liked until i stumbled across Nescafe in the aisle. To my absolute delight and surprise, it tasted as good as the real thing (you would never know there was no caffeine in it). A massive thumbs up from me.
Results.Title: As good as the real thing

Results.ReviewText: I am always looking for the middle road, when buying products, Nescafe original decaff I believe lets me sleep better at nights, as I am a very light sleeper and do not want caffeine to make matters worse.  I like the fact that it still has the full flavour of the original one and smells and tastes great and I dont have to worry about drinking too much caffeine.
Results.Title: Healthy option

Results.ReviewText: I bought this when I was pregnant as you have to limit caffeine intake in pregnancy. I tried other numerous decaf coffees but none tasted like 'the real thing' and satisfied me. Nescafe decaf coffee was fantastic - I couldn't tell the difference between decaf and the caffeinated coffee! I could have several cups a day and not worry! Thanks Nescafe!
Results.Title: Gorgeous smooth taste!

Results.ReviewText: 12 years without caffeine only with the help of great smelling good tasting coffee from nescafe. Great aroma, and I now love my daily cappucino decaf without getting the caffeine induced nausea and headaches, but we still have to buy the full fat to satisfy my partners need for a coffee kickstart. But you can't beat nescafe for a better coffee
Results.Title: Ditch the caffeine

Results.ReviewText: The last time I had tried de-caff was about 12 years ago and I didn't like it. However, recently I have had to cut down in caffeine, so decided to try again. What a difference! The flavour was great and it didn't taste like there was something missing - the caffeine. I didn't notice. Gorgeous aroma, super taste to the coast drop!
Results.Title: So flavoursome!

Results.ReviewText: Many decaf instant coffee brands have a lack of flavour - often just tasting like dirty water, but Nescafe decaf has a rich full bodied coffee flavour which is similar to the caffeinated version which is great for people like me who are unable to have caffeine, yet still love the taste of a good cup of coffee in am instant! :-)
Results.Title: Bursting with rich flavour!

Results.ReviewText: There was only Nescafe Decaf available at a meeting today so I decided to try it and was very pleasantly surprised. It was full flavoured and provided a very satisfying drink, which I was very happy to have a second cup. I would consider buying this as a daily drink but still require my caffine boost first thing in the morning.
Results.Title: Pleasantly surprising

Results.ReviewText: I only ever buy Nescafe. I buy the cappuccino sachets which I love & the normal original but this is the first time I've bought decaff after being advised by my GP to avoid caffeine due to my medication. I was wary that the flavour wouldn't be as good but I was wrong, it still has that great Nescafe flavour. Highly recommended
Results.Title: Smooth rich flavour

Results.ReviewText: As a coffee freak who panics and gets the shakes when I don't get my regular fix, I was very sceptical when my friend told me that Nescafé Original Decaff would give me all the taste and flavour I expect from my coffee. Having tried it, I can state that she was quite correct. This makes an exceptional cup of very good coffee.
Results.Title: Flavour of "Real Coffee"

Results.ReviewText: As I was having a surge in my blood pressure & heart rate with ordinary cooffee, I decided to have a punt on Nescafe decaf. And what a revelation it was! Subtle fruity flavour, lovely aroma with predominantly medium roasted arabica indulgence. Even my partner is a convert and moreover it is exceptionally good value as well .
Results.Title: Revelation

Results.ReviewText: We love our coffee and it has got to be good. As we have got older we find we need to drink the decaffeinated varieties and were concerned that we may lose some of the great flavour, but NOT so with Nescafe original decaf. It still has the pure coffee flavour and has become our favoured drink. Keep up the great work Nescafe
Results.Title: continuing great taste

Results.ReviewText: Both my wife and I use and love Nescaff Decaff. (amendment intended). Great flavour, smooth taste, and no caffeine to help us poor souls keep cholesterol and high blood pressure in check. Not too strong; not a heaped teaspoon, nor a level one. I like mine with a pinch of sugar, my wife none. Great value as always has been.
Results.Title: Title is as it should be. Nescafe, what else?

Results.ReviewText:
I have recently been diagnosed with type 2 diabetes so started on the G.I. Diet. It advises decaf coffee as ordinary coffee raises the blood glucose level. I tried various brands until I finally found Nescafé. I now use no other because of the rich aroma and satisfying taste. I gladly give it top marks. 
It is real coffee
Results.Title: Healthy advice

Results.ReviewText: Recently had to review my caffine intake due to high blood pressure, was really surprised at the taste of Nescafe Decaff. Did not know what to expect as I normally have 'full fat!' but I was really surprised to find the taste has not changed, still really rich and flavoursome. Thank you Nescafe for not stinting on taste!!
Results.Title: Rich and Flavoursome

Results.ReviewText: Taste to suit all strengths - for a really strong cup, heap the spoon - for the weaker inclined ... level or lose half a measure!  Excellent for that last night cup which won't keep you wishing you hadn't whilst trying to get to sleep.  Highly recommend - at a price that is right ... without keeping you up all night ....
Results.Title: Coffee fix without an all night billing!

Results.ReviewText: I HAVE BEING DRINKING NESCAFE DECAFF FOR OVER 10 YEARS NOW. I DECIDED THAT I WANTED TO CUT ON CAFFEINE BUT I WANTED TO KEEP FLAVOUR AND WITH NESCAFE DECAFF IS WHAT YOU GET, FULL FLAVOUR. I HAVE GIVEN NESCAFE DECAFF TO FRIENDS AND FAMILY WITHOUT THEIR KNOWLEDGE AND THEY WERE GENUELY SURPRISED WHEN TOLD IT WAS DECAFF.
Results.Title: DECAFF FULL OF FLAVOUR

Results.ReviewText: this is my go to coffee, morning, midday, and late at night! why you may ask because it's so rich and tasty, if you can't eat cake or eat a biscuit for health reason's (the deaded Big 'D'  diabetes) you have to have some pleasure in life and mine's coffee so it has to be the best! and that's Nescafe original Decaff
Results.Title: My go to Coffee alway's

Results.ReviewText: We always buy this coffee as the taste is pleasant and still tastes like real caffeinated coffee.  It dissolves easily and makes a good relaxing (no caffeine to pump you up) drink.  It is reasonably priced (depending where you buy it) compared to other brands.  We buy the larger jars as they are more economical.
Results.Title: One of the best Decaff coffees available.

Results.ReviewText: trying to be a bit more healthy as I drink lots of coffee throughout the day I gave this a try and can honestly say this tastes exactly the same as regular nescafe,I have even given it to work colleagues who are none the wiser that its not regular nescafe either so give it a try .......disappointed you wont be!
Results.Title: same great taste

Results.ReviewText: I think that this is probably the best decaf on the market, for the price you pay for it. The only thing I can add to that is the fact it tastes like real coffee. You know the stuff with caffeine in it, I found it so difficult to tell them apart that I have stopped buying real coffee at all. Well done Nescafé.
Results.Title: Tastes like coffee!

Results.ReviewText: As a lover of Nescafe coffee I thought I would give the decaff a try. I was drinking about 5 cups a day and decided that was far too much caffeine in one day, so I bought your decaff. I was pleasantly surprised as the taste was sublime. I couldn't tell the difference. Well done Nescafe! and a big thank you.
Results.Title: As good as full caff

Results.ReviewText: I had bee thinking about converting to Decaff for a while, but nothing seemed to matchup in terms of taste, then I got around to Nescafe Original, and now I won't drink anything else, excellent taste, and it hits the spot every time, no matter what you have heard about Decaff Coffee's, this is the best ...
Results.Title: I am a convert

Results.ReviewText: Decided to try this to drink on an evening and reduce our caffeine intake. It is lovely - if you like Nescafe Original then you will like this. My wife and I cannot tell the difference between it and the Original (caffeine) version. Has it helped me sleep - difficult to say for certain but I believe so.
Results.Title: Tastes great!

Results.ReviewText: I am not a great coffee lover and cannot tolerate caffeine.  However, I do find that the original Nescafe decaf is delightfully smooth and velvety, no sharpness or bitterness and most importantly no aftertaste.  Great coffee.  You can keep all your fancy coffees, plan and simple, you cannot beat it.
Results.Title: Smooth on the Palate - A delight to drink
